{{> header}}
<style>
  body {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    box-sizing: border-box;
  }

  body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #333;
    background-color: #f4f4f4;
  }

  header {
    background-color: #1584c945;
    color:  #003366;
    padding: 20px 0;
    text-align: center;
    border-radius: 25px;
    margin: 20px;
  }

  header h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
  }

  main {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 20px;
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 15px;
    color: #003366;
  }

  h3 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 30px;
    color: #003366;
  }

  p {
    margin-bottom: 15px;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  ul {
    list-style-type: disc;
    margin-left: 20px;
  }

  strong {
    font-weight: bold;
  }

  em {
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* Article Styles */
  .article-container {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 20px;
  }

  .article-block {
    width: 100%;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .article-text {
    flex: 1;
    padding: 20px;
  }

  .article-image {
    flex: 1;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .article-image img {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 600px;
    border: 5px solid #ffc0cb9c;
  }

  .article-image figcaption {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #555;
  }
  #newsletter {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column; /* Stack elements vertically */
    align-items: center; /* Center horizontally */
    justify-content: center; /* Center vertically */
    background-color: rgba(11, 111, 205, 0);
    padding: 30px 15px; 
    margin-top: 30px; 
    text-align: center;
}

.newstext h4 {
    font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
    font-weight: normal;
    font-size: 20px;
    margin-bottom: 10px; /* Reduce gap */
}

.newstext p {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: #777;
    margin-bottom: 20px; /* Adjust spacing below text */
}
.form {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 10px; /* Reduce space between input & button */
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 400px; /* Limit width for better layout */
}

/* Input field */
.form input {
    width: 70%; 
    border: none;
    border-bottom: 2px solid black; 
    outline: none;
    background: transparent;
    font-size: 16px;
    padding: 8px 5px;
    text-align: center;
}

/* Placeholder text */
.form input::placeholder {
    color: #1a0e0e;
    font-size: 14px;
}

/* Button */
.form button {
    background: black;
    color: white;
    border: none;
    padding: 5px 10px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: 0.3s ease;
}

.form button:hover {
    background: #333333aa; /* Slight hover effect */
}
</style>

<title>Trendy Textile</title>
</head>

<body>
  <header>
    <h1>Fashion Souvenirs in Bhutan</h1>
  </header>

  <main>
    <section>
      <p>
        Most visitors traveling to Bhutan are aware of what to buy or have an idea about the ordinary souvenirs 
        like wood-carved masks, traditional Mandala paintings, prayer flags, or handmade papers. But Bhutan
         offers more than just the ordinary—especially for those who love fashion and those who like to stand out.
      </p>

      <p>
        Bhutan does not fall short of creative and innovative talents who cater to fashionistas always seeking
         new inspirations to turn streets into runways. Each piece narrates a story—from traditional handlooms to
          stylish clutches. You won't just be buying a chic purse; you'll be buying stories woven with culture, 
          passion, and heritage.
      </p>

      <p>
        From repurposed textiles to cool accessories inspired by ethnicity and tradition, 
        Bhutanese fashion brings together sustainability, storytelling, and style. Below are some top 
        fashion influencers and designers in Bhutan that you should know about while visiting.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Bhutan Street Fashion (Fashion Blogger)</h2>
      <p>
        Bhutan Street Fashion is a photo-based fashion blog that finds inspiration on the streets of
         Bhutan, portraying an unfiltered sense of modernization. Its creators draw motivation from the 
         everyday lives of Bhutanese people, blending tradition with contemporary expression.
      </p>
      <p>
        Through Instagram and Facebook, the blog showcases traditional values and their evolution.
         It has inspired many Bhutanese youth to fall in love with their heritage costumes and recognize
          their cultural significance. Launched in 2010, Bhutan Street Fashion continues to grow, connecting
           Bhutanese fashion to a global audience.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>CDK: Contemporary Bhutanese Clothing Line</h2>
      <p>
        CDK is a Bhutanese contemporary casual clothing brand based in Thimphu. The name “CDK” is derived from the founder's name, Chandrika. Launched in Fall 2016, the collection incorporates Bhutanese textiles—silk and raw silk—dyed with natural pigments.
      </p>
      <p>
        The brand is committed to eco-friendly practices, challenging fashion’s status as one of the world's most polluting industries. CDK offers traditionally inspired daily wear with a modern touch. In addition to clothing, they sell stylish accessories like bags, hand clutches, belts, and stoles—perfect for travelers who want to look classy while supporting local craftsmanship.
      </p>
      <p>
        The CDK store is located just above the Craft Bazaar in the capital city, making it easily accessible for visitors.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>

  <section id="newsletter">
    <div class="newstext">
      <h4>Join Our Newsletter!</h4>
      <p>Get E-mail about our latest products and special offers</p>
    </div>
    <div class="form">
      <form>
        <input type="email" placeholder="Your Email Address" required />
        <button type="submit">Sign Up</button>
      </form>
    </div>
  </section>

  {{> footer}}
</body>
</html>
